      #iGEM Monument Challenge
       During the summer iGEM GO Paris Saclay organized the iGEM Monument Challenge. We thought that it was a really great idea and took part in it.
       [Have a look at our beautiful pictures](https://www.instagram.com/p/CSXD7c0D7bJ/). We showed the Karlsbrunnen, Aachens Cathedral and the Elisenbrunnen. 
       
       #Postcard Challenge
       As every year the iGEM Team of the Heinrich-Heine-University reached out to us offering to participate in their postcard challenge. 
       The task was to design a synthetic biology or project-related postcard and to send copies to Düsseldorf. In return, they send us postcards of the other participating teams. 
       Our postcard shows a TdT cartoon-like with DNA. We decided on this illustration because the TdT was the main enzyme for our project.
